OL,6,F"When you think about it, this being
OL,7,Fthe 80th anniversary and Bernard being
OL,8,F100, he was 20 years old, to see the
OL,9,Fhorrors of war, and he's still telling
OL,10,Fstory of the friends he lost back then
OL,11,Fand we've got to keep this story
OL,12,Fgoing," said Nancy Kay, Branch Chair
OL,13,Ffor the RBL in Crewe.
OL,15,F"Bernard loves going to the schools
OL,16,Fand talking to the children and
OL,17,Ftelling his stories, and I've been
OL,18,Fthere and the children love hearing
OL,19,Fhis stories.
