OL,6,F"When I got up, a lady came to me and
OL,7,Fshe said 'Do you know that airman?'
OL,8,Fand I said 'yes, he was one of my
OL,9,Fwireless operators' and she started
OL,10,Fcrying on my shoulder.
OL,12,F"'I'm a relative she said, I'm so
OL,13,Fpleased that somebody else is looking
OL,14,Fafter his grave' and I always think
OL,15,Fabout these lads.
OL,17,F"Whenever I go anywhere, I think about
OL,18,Fthe others but when you know them so
OL,19,Fwell it upsets me."
